obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (42054)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00028_198851_1517807324521&sectionId=42054&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00028_198851_1517807324521
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Labour Laws`
  line `(1[Simplification of Procedure for] Furnishing Returns and Maintaining Registers by certain`
  line `Establishments) Act, 1988..`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this Act, in relation to the Plantations Labour Act, 1951`
  line `(69 of 1951) shall extend to the State of Jammu and Kashmir*.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^2`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint, and different dates may be appointed for different States, and any reference in`
  line `any provision of this Act to the commencement of this Act shall be construed as a reference to the coming`
  line `into force of that provision in that State.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for "Exemption from" (w.e.f. 1-1-2015).`
  line
  line `2. 1st May, 1989, vide notification No. G.S.R.436(E), dated 10th April, 1989, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II, sec.`
  line `3(i).`
  line
  line `*. Vide notification No. S.O. 3912(E), dated 30th October, 2019, this Act is made applicable to the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir and the Union territory of Ladakh.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (42055)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 33 of 2014, s. 4, for "nineteen" (w.e.f. 1-1-2015)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00028_198851_1517807324521&sectionId=42055&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00028_198851_1517807324521
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "employer", in relation to a Scheduled Act, which defines such expression, has the same`
  line `meaning assigned to it in that Act, and in relation to any other Scheduled Act, means the person who is`
  line `required to furnish returns or maintain registers under that Act;`
  line
  line `(b) "establishment" has the meaning assigned to it in a Scheduled Act, and includes--`
  line
  line `(i) an ‘industrial or other establishment’ as defined in section 2 of the Payment of Wages Act,`
  line `1936 (4 of 1936);`
  line
  line `(ii) a "factory" as defined in section 2 of the Factories Act, 1948 (63 of 1948);`
  line
  line `(iii) a factory, workshop or place where employees are employed or work is given out to`
  line `workers, in any scheduled employment to which the Minimum Wages Act, 1948 (11 of 1948),`
  line applies;
  line
  line `(iv) a "plantation" as defined in section 2 of the Plantations Labour Act, 1951 (69 of 1951),`
  line and
  line
  line `(v) a "newspaper establishment" as defined in section 2 of the Working Journalists and other`
  line `Newspaper Employees (Conditions of Service) and Miscellaneous Provisions Act, 1955 (45 of`
  line `1955);`
  line
  line `(c) "Form" means a Form specified in the Second Schedule;`
  line
  line `(d) “Scheduled Act” means an Act specified in the First Schedule and is in force on the`
  line `commencement of this Act in the territories to which such Act extends generally, and includes the`
  line `rules made thereunder;`
  line
  line `(e) "small establishment" means an establishment in which not less than ten and not more than`
  line `^1[forty] persons are employed or were employed on any day of the preceding twelve months;`
  line
  line `(f) "very small establishment" means an establishment in which not more than nine persons are`
  line `employed or were employed on any day of the preceding twelve months.`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (42056)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Amendment of certain labour laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00028_198851_1517807324521&sectionId=42056&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00028_198851_1517807324521
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `On and from the commencement of this Act, the Scheduled`
  line `Acts shall have effect subject to the provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (42057)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Exemption from furnishing or maintaining of returns and registers required under certain labour laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 33 of 2014, s. 5, for section 4 (w.e.f. 1-1-2015).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00028_198851_1517807324521&sectionId=42057&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00028_198851_1517807324521
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `^1[4. Exemption from furnishing or maintaining of returns and registers requires under certain`
  line `labour laws.-- (1) Notwithstanding anything contained in a Scheduled Act, on and from the`
  line `commencement of the Labour Laws (Exemption from Furnishing Returns and Maintaining Registers by`
  line `certain Establishments) Amendment Act, 2014, it shall not be necessary for an employer in relation to any`
  line `small establishment or very small establishment to which a Scheduled Act applies, to furnish the returns or`
  line `to maintain the registers required to be furnished or maintained under that Scheduled Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that such employer--`
  line
  line `(a) furnishes, in lieu of such returns, annual return in Form I; and`
  line
  line `(b) maintains, in lieu of such registers,---`
  line
  line `(i) registers in Form II and Form III, in the case of small establishments, and`
  line
  line `(ii) a register in Form III, in the case of very small establishments,`
  line
  line `at the work spot:`
  line
  line `Provided further that every such employer shall continue to--`
  line
  line `(a) issue wage slips in the Form prescribed in the Minimum Wages (Central) Rules, 1950 made`
  line `under sections 18 and 30 of the Minimum Wages Act, 1948 (11 of 1948) and slips relating to`
  line `measurement of the amount of work done by piece-rated workers required to be issued under the`
  line `Payment of Wages (Mines) Rules, 1956 made under sections 13A and 26 of the Payment of Wages`
  line `Act, 1936 (4 of 1936); and`
  line
  line `(b) file returns relating to accidents under sections 88 and 88A of the Factories Act, 1948`
  line `(63 of 1948) and sections 32A and 32B of the Plantations Labour Act, 1951 (69 of 1951).`
  line
  line `(2) The annual return in Form I and the registers in Forms II and III and wage slips, wage books and`
  line `other records, as provided in sub-section (1), may be maintained by an employer either in physical form or`
  line `on a computer, computer floppy, diskette or other electronic media:`
  line
  line `Provided that in case of computer, computer floppy, diskette or other electronic form, a printout of`
  line `such returns, registers, books and records or a portion thereof is made available to the Inspector on`
  line demand.
  line
  line `(3) The employer or the person responsible to furnish the annual return in Form I may furnish it to the`
  line `Inspector or any other authority prescribed under the Scheduled Acts either in physical form or through`
  line `electronic mail if the Inspector or the authority has the facility to receive such electronic mail.`
  line
  line `(4) Save as provided in sub-section (1), all other provisions of a Scheduled Act, including, in`
  line `particular, the inspection of the registers by, and furnishing of their copies to, the authorities under that`
  line `Act, shall apply to the returns and registers required to be furnished or maintained under this Act as they`
  line `apply to the returns and registers under that Scheduled Act.`
  line
  line `(5) Where an employer in respect of an establishment referred to in sub-section (1), to whom a`
  line `Scheduled Act applies, furnishes returns or maintains the registers as provided in the proviso to sub-section`
  line `(1), nothing contained in that Scheduled Act shall render him liable to any penalty for his failure to furnish`
  line `any return or to maintain any register under that Scheduled Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (42058)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title Savings.
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00028_198851_1517807324521&sectionId=42058&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00028_198851_1517807324521
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `The commencement of this Act shall not affect--`
  line
  line `(a) the previous operation of any provision of any Scheduled Act or the validity, invalidity, effect`
  line `or consequence of anything done or suffered under that provision, before the relevant period;`
  line
  line `(b) any right, privilege, obligation or liability already acquired, accrued or incurred under any`
  line `Scheduled Act, before the relevant period;`
  line
  line `(c) any penalty, forfeiture or punishment incurred or inflicted in respect of any offence committed`
  line `under any Scheduled Act, before the relevant period;`
  line
  line `(d) any investigation, legal proceeding or remedy in respect of any such right, privilege,`
  line `obligation, liability, penalty, forfeiture or punishment aforesaid,`
  line
  line `and any such investigation, legal proceeding or remedy in respect of any such right, privilege, obligation,`
  line `liability, penalty, forfeitureor punishment shall be instituted, continued or disposed of, as the case may be,`
  line `in accordance with that Scheduled Act.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purpose of this section, the expression "relevant period" means the period`
  line `during which an establishment is or was a small establishment or a very small establishment under this`
  line Act.
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (42059)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title Penalty.
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00028_198851_1517807324521&sectionId=42059&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00028_198851_1517807324521
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `Any employer who fails to comply with the provisions of this Act shall, on conviction,`
  line `be punishable--`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of the first conviction, with fine which may extend to rupees five thousand; and`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of any second or subsequent conviction, with imprisonment for a period which shall`
  line `not be less than one month but which may extend to six months or with fine which shall not be less`
  line `than rupees ten thousand but may extend to rupees twenty-five thousand, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (42060)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Power to amend Form.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00028_198851_1517807324521&sectionId=42060&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00028_198851_1517807324521
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, if it is of opinion that it is expedient so`
  line `to do, by notification in the Official Gazette, amend any Form and thereupon such Form shall, subject to`
  line `the provisions of sub-section(2), be deemed to have been amended accordingly.`
  line
  line `(2) Any notification issued under sub-section (1) shall be laid before each House of Parliament, if it is`
  line `sitting as soon as may be after the issue of the notification, and if it is not sitting, within seven days of its`
  line `re-assembly and the Central Government shall seek the approval of Parliament to the notification by a`
  line `resolution moved within a period of fifteen days beginning with the day on which the notification is so laid`
  line `before the House of the People, and if Parliament makes any modification in the notification or directs that`
  line `the notification should cease to have effect, the notification shall thereafter have effect only in such`
  line `modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be, but without prejudice to the validity of anything`
  line `previously done thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (42061)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00028_198851_1517807324521&sectionId=42061&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00028_198851_1517807324521
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of this Act,`
  line `the Central Government may, by order, not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, remove the`
  line `difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made after the expiry of a period of two years from the date on`
  line `which this Act receives the assent of the President.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
